Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450}(chopped into 2cm wide wedges) (no need to peel). Pop them on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

While the potatoes cook, zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Put the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} in a #small bowl{}. Add the lemon zest and mix together until evenly combined. Stir in the @peri peri seasoning{1/2%tsp} (add less if you don't like heat) and a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Pour in the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}. Mix together until everything is thoroughly coated in the olive oil and the mixture is quite moist.

Line another baking tray with #baking paper{} and lay the @cod fillets{2} on top, skin-side down. Put a tsp of @mayonnaise{1} on each cod fillet and spread out to coat it. Discard any remaining mayonnaise. Spoon the crumbs onto the the fish fillets as evenly as you can and press down so they stick onto the tops.

When the wedges have been in your oven for ~{20%minutes}, move them to the middle shelf of your oven and put the fish on the top shelf to bake until the crumbs are golden and the fish is cooked, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, squeeze the lemon juice into a #large bowl{} and add the @honey{15%g}, @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Halve the @tomatoes{1}(halved), pop them in the bowl with the dressing and add the @baby leaf mix{50%g}, gently toss together. Leave to one side.

When the fish is ready, it's time to dish up! Carefully remove the fish from the tray and place onto your plates, share out the wedges and serve the salad on the side. Add a dollop of @tomato ketchup{1%tsp}. Enjoy!